# SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0
# Adjustfile — Drift-tolerance contract for F19 Stealth Glider
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell (hyperpolymath)
#
# Cumulative-drift catchment: tolerance bands + corrective actions.
# Authority: advisory (Yard) — continue-with-warnings.
# Run with: just contracts

@abstract:
Drift tolerances and corrective actions for F19 Stealth Glider. Unlike MUST
(hard gate), ADJUST tracks cumulative drift against tolerance bands and
proposes corrective actions. Advisory — it warns and trends, it does not block.
@end

## Design Drift

### substrate-purity
- description: Nothing in the tree special-cases a cell or scripts a mover
- tolerance: 0 entity tables, per-cell exceptions, or hard-coded movement paths in engine.mjs
- corrective: Express the behaviour as a real Life pattern, or drop it (D-01)
- severity: advisory

### fiction-count
- description: Exactly one departure from pure Life is admitted — the pre-contact player overlay
- tolerance: 1 declared fiction, documented in README.md and VERIFICATION.md
- corrective: Either eliminate the new fiction or document and justify it in the ledger
- severity: advisory
- notes: Undeclared fictions are how a substrate quietly becomes scenery.

### difficulty-source
- description: Difficulty comes from reading phase and geometry, not from execution speed
- tolerance: 0 timing windows narrower than one glider period (4 generations)
- corrective: Widen the window or move the challenge back into geometry
- severity: advisory

## Verification Drift

### ledger-script-correspondence
- description: Every VERIFICATION.md claim cites a script that exists and runs
- tolerance: 0 claims citing a missing script, a transcript, or "see above"
- corrective: Write the script, or restate the claim as an argued disclosure
- severity: advisory
- notes: Claim #3 was once cited to a transcript rather than a script; verify3.mjs now discharges it.

### ci-runs-what-is-cited
- description: The CI ledger and the VERIFICATION.md citations do not diverge
- tolerance: CI runs every cited script; exploratory scripts stay excluded
- corrective: Reconcile .github/workflows/ci.yml with the ledger table
- severity: advisory

### exploratory-script-health
- description: Exploratory scripts still execute, even though their findings are negative
- tolerance: 0 exploratory scripts that crash rather than reporting "no viable candidate"
- corrective: Fix the harness. A crash is a bug; a negative result is a finding.
- severity: advisory
- notes: verify3 and verify9 both once crashed with `stamp out of bounds` on negative lanes. That was a harness bug masquerading as a result.

## Documentation Drift

### state-freshness
- description: STATE.a2ml tracks the real phase and component status
- tolerance: STATE.a2ml last-updated within one milestone of HEAD
- corrective: Refresh .machine_readable/descriptiles/STATE.a2ml from README.md + VERIFICATION.md
- severity: advisory

### settled-questions-stay-settled
- description: Closed questions are not silently reopened
- tolerance: 0 new work re-deriving the stream no-go lemma or re-testing overlap-only contact
- corrective: Point the work at STATE.a2ml [settled-questions] and stop
- severity: advisory

### readme-ledger-agreement
- description: README.md's stated results match VERIFICATION.md
- tolerance: 0 numeric disagreements (0/30, 21/30, 9/30, 30/30, 15 vs ~17 units)
- corrective: The ledger wins; correct the README
- severity: advisory

## Repository Drift

### spdx-header-consistency
- description: All committed source and metadata files carry an SPDX header
- tolerance: 0 files missing SPDX-License-Identifier
- corrective: Add the correct header — AGPL-3.0-or-later for code, MPL-2.0 for .a2ml
- severity: advisory

### dependency-creep
- description: The project stays dependency-free
- tolerance: 0 entries under dependencies or devDependencies
- corrective: Remove the dependency, or record a decision superseding D-08
- severity: advisory

### bundle-freshness
- description: The committed bundle tracks src/
- tolerance: 0 commits touching src/ that leave f19-stealth-glider.html unchanged
- corrective: Run `just build` and commit the regenerated bundle
- severity: advisory

### workflow-pin-drift
- description: Workflow action pins remain full commit SHAs
- tolerance: 0 `uses:` referencing a tag or branch
- corrective: Re-pin to a SHA with a version comment; the org rejects tags with startup_failure
- severity: advisory
